{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, the attention and contextual value of each point in a sequence is used to generate a representation that is decoded to provide a tangible output.",
    "A familiar example is the generative pre-trained transformer (GPT) model (Radford et al. 2019; Brown et al. 2020), popularly used for text-to-text and text-to-image translation.",
    "For example, if we have a database containing the input question \"Are you ok?\"",
    "and various outputs, such as \"I am fine\" or \"I am sad\" the transformer will learn the likeliest response sequence.",
    "For example on the local scale, it may be that the majority of answers begin with \"I am\", so this is first selected as the start of the output."
  ]
}